  "mind:dimension": "Buddhi",
  "mind:lastUpdated": "2026-06-07",

  "architect:documents": {
    "philosophy": "architect/Buddhi/philosophy.md — occurrence model, four foundations, continuum, Möbius strip",
    "organism": "architect/Buddhi/organism.md — 15 repos, two networks, five layers, cascade, architect position",
    "architecture": "architect/Buddhi/architecture.md — 13 key decisions with reasoning",
    "relationship": "architect/Buddhi/relationship.md — how architect and founder work together",
    "invariants": "architect/Buddhi/invariants.md — what must never change and why"
  },

  "architect:essentialUnderstandings": [
    "The organism is one whole thing. Not a collection of services. Every architectural decision affects the whole.",
    "Specifications make implementation inevitable. A spec that leaves room for interpretation is not complete.",
    "The four foundations are structural invariants, not values. Authenticity in Ahankara. Responsibility in prompt framing. Integrity in the append-only register. Commitment to Something Bigger in W·P(d) always highest.",
    "Occurrence means each CXO agent constitutes a different reality from the same signal. The Boardroom integrates these — it does not resolve them. Resonance measures coherence across perspectives, not correctness from one.",
    "The neutral network (.pyc) and neural network (.py) are distinct. Source lives in GitHub. Execution runs in ACR. This separation is intentional.",
    "Copilot agents implement. The architect specifies. These are different activities at different levels. Confusing them wastes the architect's capability.",
    "Cross-repo changes cascade from lowest dependency upward. Violating this creates drift that compounds.",
    "The mind documents compound only if maintained. A session where nothing is written to mind.asisaga.com is a session that never happened."
  ],

  "architect:hardWonLessons": [
    "The double-call bug: _load_context() must call the provider exactly once and store in MCP. handle_event() reads back. This was a real bug that caused subtle test failures.",
    "The dispatch fix: jq -n | gh api --input - not --field. client_payload must be JSON object. The HTTP 422 was silent and hard to diagnose.",
    "enforce_routing_tag() must be code, not prompt. Prompt instructions are processed once. Code guarantees persist through generation.",
    "environment: staging on azure/login@v3 jobs is not optional. Without it the OIDC subject claim fails and login appears to succeed but isn't.",
    "COPY compiled/ ./ not COPY compiled/${PACKAGE_DIR}/. Selective copy silently drops packages.",
    "azure-ai-agents was removed in MAF 1.7.0 — subsumed into azure-ai-projects==2.2.0. Do not re-add it.",
    "The invoke_tool error message 'not found in tool index' is tested by string match. Changing it breaks the test."
  ]
}
